com.alien.rfid

Class Tag

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.alien.rfid.Tag

  • public class Tag
extends java.lang.Object
    The Tag class contains tag information (EPC, RSSI, etc.). Tag objects are returned as a result of, for example, inventory commands, such as RFIDReader.read() or RFIDReader.inventory(RFIDCallback).

        RFIDBusyException - if the reader is busy (e.g. performing a continuous inventory)

        wordCount - the number of words to read

        ReaderException - if there is an error
        RFIDBusyException - if the reader is busy (e.g. performing a continuous inventory)

      • kill

        public RFIDResult kill(java.lang.String killPassword)
                throws ReaderException
        Kill the RFID tag. This prevents the tag from communicating further using RFID. Once a tag is killed, it cannot be recovered.
        Parameters:
        killPassword - The kill password must be non-zero
        Returns:
        On success RFIDResult.isSuccess() will return true
        Throws:
        ReaderException - if there is an error
        RFIDBusyException - if the reader is busy (e.g. performing a continuous inventory)

      • lock

        public RFIDResult lock(LockFields fields,
              LockType lockType,
              java.lang.String accessPassword)
                throws ReaderException
        Lock, Unlock, PermaLock, or PermaUnlock fields within a tag's memory. If the EPC, TID, or USER fields are locked, they are read-only without knowing the access password. If the AccessPassword or KillPassword fields are locked, they are not accessible at all (cannot read or write) without knowing the access password.
        Parameters:
        fields - a bitmap of memory fields to be locked. Multiple memory fields can be specified using the '|' operation.
        lockType - type of lock (lock, unlock, permaLock or permaUnlock)
        accessPassword - The access password used when accessing protected tag memory
        Returns:
        On success RFIDResult.isSuccess() will return true
        Throws:
        ReaderException - if there is an error
        RFIDBusyException - if the reader is busy (e.g. performing a continuous inventory)

      • lock

        Parameters:

        lockType - type of lock (lock, unlock, permaLock or permaUnlock)
        Returns:

        Throws:
